{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LxgrAVmhhovqJyqKkBejxN","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Implement `ralph-burning` v1 Rewrite\n     2→\n     3→## 1) Objective and Source of Truth\n     4→You are implementing a greenfield Rust rewrite of the orchestrator in `ralph-burning-rewrite/`. The existing code in `multibackend-orchestration/` is **read-only reference-only** for behavior inference; do not preserve or migrate legacy `.ralph` state, artifact formats, loop directories, or git checkpoint encoding.\n     5→\n     6→## 2) Product Definition\n     7→Build a modular monolith called `ralph-burning` with one binary and these hard constraints:\n     8→- Rust implementation.\n     9→- New workspace root is `.ralph-burning/`.\n    10→- Built-in flow presets are exactly: `standard`, `quick_dev`, `docs_change`, `ci_improvement`.\n    11→- No arbitrary user-defined flow DSL in v1.\n    12→- Markdown is only a rendered, human-readable artifact, not workflow protocol.\n    13→- Canonical workflow state is structured stage payload JSON + run state + journal.\n    14→- Runtime logs are ephemeral and never part of durable project history.\n    15→\n    16→## 3) Non-goals\n    17→- No compatibility layer for old `.ralph` workspaces or legacy reconstruction logic.\n    18→- No service-oriented microservice split in v1.\n    19→- No full implementation of every slice before completing core canonical state and shared engine.\n    20→\n    21→## 4) Canonical Vocabulary (must use consistently)\n    22→- `workspace`: orchestration root `.ralph-burning/`\n    23→- `project`: durable work item with immutable `flow`\n    24→- `run`: execution instance for a project\n    25→- `stage`: named step in a flow preset\n    26→- `stage cursor`: current stage + cycle + attempt metadata\n    27→- `work cycle`: unit of iterative delivery work\n    28→- `completion round`: unit deciding complete vs continue\n    29→- `backend family`: e.g., Claude, Codex, OpenRouter\n    30→- `stage contract`: schema + required fields + semantic validation rules\n    31→- `stage payload`: validated structured output\n    32→- `history artifact`: rendered Markdown derived from payload\n    33→- `runtime log`: operational/debug output\n    34→- `journal`: append-only domain event log\n    35→- `rollback point`: durable logical checkpoint\n    36→- `task`: daemon unit of automated work\n    37→\n    38→Decision in this prompt:\n    39→- Use canonical term `cycle` in public docs and CLI; accept `loop` as deprecated alias only for informational output, not as a primary API term.\n    40→\n    41→## 5) Bounded Contexts (required)\n    42→Implement the following context packages with ports/adapters boundaries:\n    43→\n    44→- `contexts/workspace_governance/*`\n    45→- `contexts/project_run_record/*`\n    46→- `contexts/workflow_composition/*`\n    47→- `contexts/agent_execution/*`\n    48→- `contexts/requirements_drafting/*`\n    49→- `contexts/automation_runtime/*`\n    50→- `contexts/conformance_spec/*`\n    51→- `adapters/*` for side effects\n    52→\n    53→Primary dependencies:\n    54→- `workspace_governance` is upstream for config and flow discovery.\n    55→- `project_run_record` is source of durable truth.\n    56→- `workflow_composition` drives run progression.\n    57→- `agent_execution` provides invocation + normalized structured results.\n    58→- `automation_runtime` consumes routing and dispatches into workflow/requirements.\n    59→\n    60→## 6) Folder and Storage Layout\n    61→Use this model in `ralph-burning-rewrite/`:\n    62→\n    63→`src/`\n    64→- `main.rs`\n    65→- composition, shared, contexts, adapters, etc. as per provided package sketch.\n    66→\n    67→`.ralph-burning/`\n    68→- `workspace.toml`\n    69→- `active-project`\n    70→- `projects/<project-id>/project.toml`\n    71→- `projects/<project-id>/prompt.md`\n    72→- `projects/<project-id>/run.json`\n    73→- `projects/<project-id>/journal.ndjson`\n    74→- `projects/<project-id>/sessions.json`\n    75→- `projects/<project-id>/history/payloads/*`\n    76→- `projects/<project-id>/history/artifacts/*`\n    77→- `projects/<project-id>/runtime/logs/*`\n    78→- `projects/<project-id>/runtime/backend/*`\n    79→- `projects/<project-id>/runtime/temp/*`\n    80→- `projects/<project-id>/amendments/*`\n    81→- `projects/<project-id>/rollback/*`\n    82→- `requirements/<requirements-run-id>/*`\n    83→- `daemon/tasks/*`\n    84→- `daemon/leases/*`\n    85→\n    86→You must persist:\n    87→- canonical project metadata and active run state\n    88→- payload records and payload-derived artifacts\n    89→- journal and runtime-log metadata/indexes\n    90→- rollback points and amendment queue\n    91→\n    92→## 7) Core Invariants (MUST pass)\n    93→- Each project has one immutable flow preset.\n    94→- Every active run has one stage cursor.\n    95→- Stage cursor stage must belong to the project’s selected flow.\n    96→- Cycle and completion round numbers are monotonic and independent.\n    97→- Structured payload validation must happen before any state mutation.\n    98→- Domain validation must happen after schema validation, before transition commit.\n    99→- Durable project history = journal + payloads + rendered artifacts only.\n   100→- Runtime logs are never promoted into durable history.\n   101→- Starting `run start` on a project with an active run must resume or fail with explicit message; it must not create duplicate active runs.\n   102→- Resume is allowed only from durable stage boundaries.\n   103→- Terminal state transitions persist before cleanup of external side effects when possible.\n   104→- Explicit model overrides trump role defaults.\n   105→- Session reuse only for roles/backends that explicitly allow it.\n   106→- Cancellation and timeout must immediately halt retries for the run/call.\n   107→- One writer lock per project.\n   108→- One active daemon task per issue.\n   109→- One worktree lease per task.\n   110→- Command-based routing overrides label-based routing; label overrides repo default.\n   111→- Hard rollback: logical rollback must happen before repository reset.\n   112→- Unsupported workspace versions fail fast with no implicit migration.\n   113→\n   114→## 8) CLI Contract (v1 surface)\n   115→All commands exit non-zero on invalid state or policy failures.\n   116→\n   117→Workspace/config:\n   118→- `ralph-burning init`\n   119→- `ralph-burning config show`\n   120→- `ralph-burning config get <key>`\n   121→- `ralph-burning config set <key> <value>`\n   122→- `ralph-burning config edit`\n   123→\n   124→Flow discovery:\n   125→- `ralph-burning flow list`\n   126→- `ralph-burning flow show <flow-id>`\n   127→\n   128→Projects:\n   129→- `ralph-burning project create --id <id> --name <name> --prompt <file> --flow <flow-id>`\n   130→- `ralph-burning project select <id>`\n   131→- `ralph-burning project list`\n   132→- `ralph-burning project show [<id>]`\n   133→- `ralph-burning project delete <id>`\n   134→\n   135→Run lifecycle:\n   136→- `ralph-burning run start`\n   137→- `ralph-burning run resume`\n   138→- `ralph-burning run status`\n   139→- `ralph-burning run history`\n   140→- `ralph-burning run tail [--logs]`\n   141→- `ralph-burning run rollback --to <target> [--hard]`\n   142→\n   143→Requirements:\n   144→- `ralph-burning requirements draft --idea \"<text>\"`\n   145→- `ralph-burning requirements quick --idea \"<text>\"`\n   146→- `ralph-burning requirements show <run-id>`\n   147→- `ralph-burning requirements answer <run-id>`\n   148→\n   149→Daemon:\n   150→- `ralph-burning daemon start`\n   151→- `ralph-burning daemon status`\n   152→- `ralph-burning daemon abort <task-id>`\n   153→- `ralph-burning daemon retry <task-id>`\n   154→- `ralph-burning daemon reconcile`\n   155→\n   156→Conformance:\n   157→- `ralph-burning conformance list`\n   158→- `ralph-burning conformance run [--filter <scenario-id>]`\n   159→\n   160→Clarifications for CLI behavior:\n   161→- `run tail` shows durable history only by default.\n   162→- `run tail --logs` appends latest runtime logs.\n   163→- `loop` is accepted only as a user-facing alias; `cycle` is canonical in docs and output schema.\n   164→\n   165→## 9) Built-in Flow Presets (v1)\n   166→Flows are fixed per project at creation and cannot change.\n   167→Flow stages are deterministic and configured in code:\n   168→- `standard`: `prompt_review` (optional by config) → `planning` → `implementation` → `qa` → `review` → `completion_panel` → `acceptance_qa` → `final_review` (preset-driven)\n   169→- `quick_dev`: `plan_and_implement` → `review` → `apply_fixes` → `final_review`\n   170→- `docs_change`: `docs_plan` → `docs_update` → `docs_validation` → `review`\n   171→- `ci_improvement`: `ci_plan` → `ci_update` → `ci_validation` → `review`\n   172→\n   173→Validation profile and final review defaults:\n   174→- `standard`: final review enabled.\n   175→- `quick_dev`: final review enabled, lightweight panel.\n   176→- `docs_change`: final review disabled by default.\n   177→- `ci_improvement`: final review disabled by default.\n   178→\n   179→Validation profiles include all required checks named in each preset’s default profile and may add policy-specific stricter checks when explicitly configured.\n   180→\n   181→## 10) Structured Stage Contracts (mandatory)\n   182→For every supported stage:\n   183→- Define `StageContract` with JSON schema.\n   184→- Persist raw backend output for diagnostics.\n   185→- Validate payload schema first.\n   186→- Apply semantic domain validation second.\n   187→- Render Markdown deterministically from payload after successful validation.\n   188→- Do not parse Markdown for state transitions.\n   189→- Persist both payload and rendered artifact atomically under project history.\n   190→\n   191→Retry and failure classes must be explicit:\n   192→- transport failure\n   193→- schema validation failure\n   194→- domain-validation failure\n   195→- timeout\n   196→- cancellation\n   197→- qa/review outcome failure\n   198→Different classes must map to distinct retry/terminal policies.\n   199→\n   200→## 11) Project and Run Record Rules"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01X5aLsQAFgiJ96xUkfjGDzF","session_id":"4dd21658-c77f-461a-9d96-b900bdfee06f","uuid":"998e6b79-9497-417c-ab35-a2479f0b36f1"}
