ow engine\n- Make flow presets first-class (not runtime selection)\n- Use structured JSON payloads + durable history\n- Bounded context architecture with hexagonal adapters\n- Clear separation of durable vs ephemeral state\n\n### **7. Existing Implementation (Legacy)**\n\n**Major Features Implemented in Multibackend-Orchestration:**\n\n**Workflow Orchestration:**\n- Standard delivery flow (8 stages including final review)\n- Quick-dev flow (4 stages)\n- PRD/requirements workflows\n- Daemon-driven GitHub automation\n\n**Backend Support:**\n- Claude backend integration\n- Codex (OpenAI) backend\n- OpenRouter backend\n- Mock backend for testing\n- Tmux-based execution environment\n- Output normalization across backends\n\n**Project Management:**\n- Project creation/deletion/selection\n- Run lifecycle (resume, rollback)\n- Amendment queue system\n- Git worktree integration\n- Checkpoint/commit logic\n\n**Daemon Capabilities:**\n- GitHub issue processing\n- PR review automation\n- Interactive PRD generation\n- Rebase agent\n- Refinement system\n- Task scheduling with labels\n\n**Conformance Suite:**\n- 38+ test files covering:\n  - Command execution\n  - E2E workflows\n  - Daemon concurrency\n  - Backend execution\n  - PRD generation\n  - PR lifecycle\n  - Streaming\n  - Final review\n  - And more\n\n### **8. Git Status**\n\n**Current Branch:** `ralph/ralph-burning-rewrite`\n\n**Recent Commits:**\n1. `24e71fe` - \"Add legacy codebase reference, rewrite spec, and ralph config\" (added rb.md, ralph.toml, prompt files)\n2. `2e56452` - \"sync initial prompt inputs\" (synced prompt)\n3. `37c7450` - \"Initial commit\"\n\n**Status:** 2 commits ahead of origin/master, untracked files in `.ralph/tmp/`\n\n### **9. ralph-burning-rewrite/ Directory**\n\n**Location:** `/root/new-ralph-burning/ralph-burning-rewrite/`\n\n**Current State:** EMPTY - no implementation yet. This is the target for the greenfield rewrite.\n\n### **Summary of What Needs to Be Built**\n\nThe rewrite task is to